Vice President Joe Biden and Dr. Jill Biden visited Brooke Army Medical Center in San Antonio, Texas. They spent time with rehabilitating servicemembers at the Center for the Intrepid, many of whom were injured in Iraq and Afghanistan. The Bidens also met with military doctors, nurses, and staff to thank them for their care. They concluded their visit by spending time with inpatients and their families and expressing gratitude for their service and sacrifice. The Center for the Intrepid is a rehabilitation facility that treats amputees and burn victims, specifically those who have served in Iraq and Afghanistan. Veterans from previous conflicts and military personnel injured in other situations are also eligible for treatment.